L'chayim (literally, "to [[life]]") is a [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] [[Toast (honor)|toast]] and an expression of goodwill. In [[United States|American]] [[Popular culture|popular culture]], the phrase was granted a wide audience through the [[song]] (also titled '''L'chayim''') in the [[musical]] [[Fiddler on the Roof]].

